<title>BAHRAIN: Saudi Investment Bank Q1 net profit rises.</title>
<headline>Saudi Investment Bank Q1 net profit rises.</headline>
<dateline>MANAMA 1997-04-26</dateline>
<text>
<p>Three months to March 31, 1997</p>
<p>			(in millions of Saudi riyals)</p>
<p> Net profit		   44.2    vs	24.9</p>
<p> Operating income	  175.6    vs     141.7</p>
<p> Operating expenses	131.5    vs     116.9</p>
<p> Shareholders' equity  1,315.9    vs     538.4</p>
<p> Total deposits	  6,803.0    vs   6,554.1</p>
<p> Total assets	    9,855.0    vs   8,476.9</p>
<p>Full Name: The Saudi Investment Bank.</p>
<p>Note - The Riyadh-based bank is owned by Saudi investors and several Saudi and foreign banks including Chase Manhattan Corp and Industrial Bank of Japan Ltd.</p>
<p>Bahrain newsroom - 973-536187</p>
